---
title: Le Wagon 2-hour landing workshop
---

<%= partial "components/banner" %>


<div class="container-fluid readme">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1">

      <section class="readme-section">
        <h2 class="readme-header">1. Let's set up</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Start Sublime Text. It will open a new black window.</li>
          <li>Create a <strong>folder</strong> <code>landingpage</code> on your Desktop. Drag & drop this folder in the Sublime Text window.</li>
          <li>
            In Sublime Text left navigation:
            <ul>
              <li>Right click <strong>"New file"</strong></li>
              <li>Save it as <code>index.html</code> with <strong>Cmd + S</strong> or <strong>Ctrl + S</strong></li>
              <li>Do the same to create a <code>style.css</code> file</li>
              <li>Then <strong>"New Folder"</strong> and create an <code>images</code> folder</li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Finally double click on <code>index.html</code> to open it with Chrome</li>
        </ol>

        <img src='images/setup.png' width="100%"/>
      </section>

      <section class="readme-section">
        <h2 class="readme-header">2. Add some HTML content</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            To save time, just right-click on the following images and save them in your <code>images</code> folder
            <ul class="list-inline">
              <li><img src="images/focus.jpg" alt="" width="100"></li>
              <li><img src="images/attitude.jpg" alt="" width="100"></li>
              <li><img src="images/excellence.jpg" alt="" width="100"></li>
              <li><img src="images/innovative.jpg" alt="" width="100"></li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Then start with this HTML code in <code>index.html</code></li>
        </ul>
<% code("html") do %>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Values at Satair</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Our values</h1>
    <p>This is the important line everyone reads..</p>
    <p>
      <a href="#">Start now</a>
    </p>

    <img src="images/focus.jpg" alt="picture description" width="100">
    <h2>Fast</h2>
    <p>A fast app, <strong>very fast</strong> app</p>

    <img src="images/attitude.jpg" alt="picture description" width="100">
    <h2>Simple</h2>
    <p>A simple app, <strong>very simple</strong> app</p>

    <img src="images/excellence.jpg" alt="picture description" width="100">
    <h2>Awesome</h2>
    <p>An awesome app, <strong>very awesome</strong> app</p>

    <img src="images/innovative.jpg" alt="picture description" width="100">
    <h2>Beautiful</h2>
    <p>A beautiful app, <strong>very beautiful</strong> app</p>

    <p>These are our values @ Satair</p>
  </body>
</html>
<% end %>
      </section>

      <section class="readme-section">
        <h2 class="readme-header">3. CSS for fonts & colors</h2>
        <p>Link your stylesheet <code>style.css</code> in the <code>head</code> section of your HTML</p>


<% code("html") do %>
<head>
  <link href='style.css' rel='stylesheet'>
</head>
<% end %>
        <p>Then add some CSS code  in <code>style.css</code>. For some inspiration see below :-)
        <ul>
          <li>You can find nice colors on <a href="https://coolors.co/" target="_blank">Coolors</a> or <a href="http://colorhunt.co/" target="_blank">Color Hunt</a></li>
          <li>The official Satair color is <code>#B11116</code></li>
        </ul>
<% code("css") do %>
/* style.css */
body{
  font-size: 15px;
  font-family: Helvetica;
}
h1{
  font-family: Courier;
  color: red;
  font-size: 20px;
}
h2 {
  font-family: Courier;
  color: pink;
  font-size: 18px;
}
a {
  color: green;
  text-decoration: none;
}
a:hover {
  color: purple;
}
<% end %>
      </section>
      <section class="readme-section">
        <h2 class="readme-header">4. Wrap with <code>div</code></h2>
        <p>Wrap different sections in different <code>div</code></p>

<% code("html") do %>
<div>
  <h1>Our values</h1>
  <p>This is the important line everyone reads..</p>
</div>

<div>
  <img src="images/focus.jpg" alt="picture description" width="100">
  <h2>Fast</h2>
  <p>A fast app, <strong>very fast</strong> app</p>
</div>

<div>
  <img src="images/attitude.jpg" alt="picture description" width="100">
  <h2>Simple</h2>
  <p>A simple app, <strong>very simple</strong> app</p>
</div>

<div>
  <img src="images/excellence.jpg" alt="picture description" width="100">
  <h2>Awesome</h2>
  <p>An awesome app, <strong>very awesome</strong> app</p>
</div>

<div>
  <img src="images/innovative.jpg" alt="picture description" width="100">
  <h2>Beautiful</h2>
  <p>A beautiful app, <strong>very beautiful</strong> app</p>
</div>

<div>
  <p>These are our values @ Satair</p>
</div>
<% end %>

      </section>
      <section class="readme-section">
        <h2 class="readme-header">5. Name your tags</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Name your header and footer with <code>id</code> like <code>&lt;div id="header"&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;div id="footer"&gt;</code></li>
          <li>Name your values with <code>class</code> like <code>&lt;div class="value"&gt;</code></li>
          <li>Then add this nice CSS code</li>
        </ul>
<% code("css") do %>
#header{
  text-align: center;
  background-image: url('http://resources.mynewsdesk.com/image/upload/c_limit,dpr_2.0,f_auto,h_700,q_auto,w_670/c0nw0keg8aajgdojgn5u.jpg');
  background-size: cover;
  padding: 150px;
  color: white;
  text-shadow: 1px 1px 5px black;
}
#header h1 {
  color: white;
  font-size: 50px;
}
#header p {
  color: white;
  opacity: 0.8;
  font-size: 30px;
}
#footer{
  padding: 30px;
  background: rgb(30, 30, 30);
  color: rgb(240,240,240);
}
.value{
  padding: 50px;
  text-align: center;
}
<% end %>

<h3>Extra - find a cool background image</h3>
<ul>
  <li>You can pick a different background picture at <a href="http://mediaroom.satair.com/latest_media" target="_blank">Satair Media</a></li>
</ul>
      </section>
      <section class="readme-section">
        <h2 class="readme-header">6. Fontawesome</h2>
        <p>In your <code>head</code>, it's in your <code>head</code>!</p>
<% code("html") do %>
<head>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.4.0/css/font-awesome.min.css">
</head>
<% end %>
        <p>And then in the footer</p>
<% code("html") do %>
<ul>
  <li><a href="#"><i class="fa fa-youtube"></i></a></li>
  <li><a href="#"><i class="fa fa-facebook"></i></a></li>
  <li><a href="#"><i class="fa fa-twitter"></i></a></li>
  <li><a href="#"><i class="fa fa-github"></i></a></li>
</ul>
<% end %>
        <p>With a bit of CSS style</p>
<% code("css") do %>
#footer a {
  color: lightgrey;
  font-size: 25px;
}
#footer a:hover {
  color: #B11116;
}
<% end %>
      </section>
      <section class="readme-section">
        <h2 class="readme-header">7. Bootstrap setup</h2>

        <p>Link Bootstrap stylesheet in the <code>head</code> section of your HTML <strong>before your stylesheet link</strong></p>
<% code("html") do %>
<head>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.2.0/css/bootstrap.min.css">
</head>
<% end %>
          <p>Play with <code>class="btn btn-success"</code> and <code>class="list-inline"</code>, your first Bootstrap classes</p>

      </section>
      <section class="readme-section">
        <h2 class="readme-header">8. Bootstrap grid</h2>
